84.8	Philip_Zimbardo	Philip Zimbardo	Philip George Zimbardo (born March 23, 1933) is a psychologist and a professor emeritus at Stanford University. He is president of the Heroic Imagination Project. He is known for his Stanford prison study and authorship of various introductory psychology books and textbooks for college students, including The Lucifer Effect and The Time Paradox.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Zimbardo_in_Warsaw_2009.jpg/220px-Zimbardo_in_Warsaw_2009.jpg
